# Breastfeeding & Pumping Systems

This reflects a system that worked while navigating newborn feeding, pumping, and returning to work with limited time and energy.

A curated set of resources, tools, and practical systems for feeding a baby while navigating real constraints: recovery, sleep, work, and time.

The goal is not a perfect feeding journey.  
The goal is a system that supports both the baby and the mother.

---

## Core Principles

- Feeding is both biological and logistical  
- Systems reduce stress more than intentions  
- Flexibility is necessary (plans will change)  
- Maternal wellbeing is part of the system  

---

